results.occurrenceRemarks: Trying to see if I could ID these ants to genera, I stumbled on AntWeb. Wow. But, it did not help me! The keycap from my keychain is about 2 inches long - I placed it in the pictures to give a sense of size. These medium-sized ants were carrying small pieces of dry vegetation across the trail, I'd guess stalks of grasses. Interesting behavior. I observed them just past the junction of the Clarkia and the Serpentine trails, in some open grassland bordering on chaparral.
